WEBVTT

00:00:02.706 --> 00:00:04.308
<i>[singing voice] Aniplex.</i>

00:00:08.083 --> 00:00:09.452
[car door opens]

00:00:09.520 --> 00:00:11.924
<i>[Tatsuya] All right,</i>
<i>I'll be heading out now.</i>

00:00:12.224 --> 00:00:13.326
<i>[Man] Good night.</i>

00:00:25.117 --> 00:00:28.323
[whooshing]

00:00:30.193 --> 00:00:31.697
<i>[Tatsuya] Three intruders.</i>

00:00:32.131 --> 00:00:33.634
<i>[gasps]</i>
<i>That's...</i>

00:00:34.268 --> 00:00:35.672
[exhales, grunts]

00:00:44.790 --> 00:00:46.059
<i>It's not fast enough.</i>

00:00:48.129 --> 00:00:50.000
[glass shattering]
[all grunting]

00:00:50.067 --> 00:00:52.238
[electric sparking]
[all shouting]

00:00:52.304 --> 00:00:54.308
[all groaning]

00:00:55.444 --> 00:00:56.479
[grunts]

00:00:56.981 --> 00:00:58.149
[gasps]

00:01:01.624 --> 00:01:02.726
[gasps]

00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:04.362
[Mikihiko] Who's out there?

00:01:05.464 --> 00:01:07.368
<i>Who was it that came</i>
<i>to my aid?</i>

00:01:09.606 --> 00:01:11.577
[Tatsuya] Mikihiko.
It's me.

00:01:14.683 --> 00:01:16.452
[gasps]
Tatsuya?

00:01:16.921 --> 00:01:18.290
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:01:18.356 --> 00:01:19.826
<i>♪♪ That's rising hope ♪♪</i>

00:01:19.893 --> 00:01:21.864
<i>♪♪ Hey welcome</i>
<i>to our special rising ♪♪</i>

00:01:21.931 --> 00:01:24.435
<i>♪♪ Can you distance standby</i>
<i>Here we go ♪♪</i>

00:01:24.503 --> 00:01:27.575
<i>[LiSA's "Rising Hope"]</i>

00:01:27.642 --> 00:01:29.045
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:01:29.111 --> 00:01:31.984
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:01:32.051 --> 00:01:39.198
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:01:49.285 --> 00:01:51.724
<i>♪♪ Pay attention</i>
<i>Hey what is it ♪♪</i>

00:01:51.790 --> 00:01:54.462
<i>♪♪ Watch your step now ♪♪</i>
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:01:54.529 --> 00:01:56.767
<i>♪♪ Are you serious</i>
<i>No, no, no, don't worry ♪♪</i>

00:01:56.834 --> 00:01:57.569
<i>♪♪ One two three ♪♪</i>

00:01:57.636 --> 00:02:00.742
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:02:00.808 --> 00:02:07.722
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:23.219 --> 00:02:24.556
<i>♪♪ I'm feeling magical ♪♪</i>

00:02:24.623 --> 00:02:27.696
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:02:27.762 --> 00:02:32.906
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:32.972 --> 00:02:35.912
<i>♪♪ I seen my hope ♪♪</i>
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:02:35.978 --> 00:02:41.557
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:41.623 --> 00:02:43.661
<i>♪♪ That's rising hope ♪♪</i>

00:02:43.728 --> 00:02:45.832
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:49.405 --> 00:02:51.910
[footsteps approaching]

00:02:52.344 --> 00:02:54.081
[Tatsuya] He's still alive.

00:02:54.148 --> 00:02:55.518
Expertly done.

00:02:55.585 --> 00:02:56.887
Huh?

00:02:57.287 --> 00:02:58.724
From a blind position,

00:02:58.791 --> 00:03:00.995
you neutralized your targets
in one shot

00:03:01.062 --> 00:03:03.199
without fatally wounding them.

00:03:03.266 --> 00:03:05.203
‐ [grunts]
‐ [Tatsuya] The best outcome.

00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:06.840
[Yoshida grunts]

00:03:07.241 --> 00:03:09.478
Maybe, but if you hadn't
just come to my aid,

00:03:09.546 --> 00:03:11.182
they would have shot me.

00:03:11.249 --> 00:03:12.619
‐ [Tatsuya] Idiot.
‐ [gasps]

00:03:13.153 --> 00:03:14.756
[Tatsuya]
That's just conjecture.

00:03:14.823 --> 00:03:17.061
You successfully captured
these intruders

00:03:17.127 --> 00:03:18.329
with your magic.

00:03:18.396 --> 00:03:20.100
That's the only fact
that matters.

00:03:20.167 --> 00:03:21.670
[gasps]

00:03:22.171 --> 00:03:23.674
[Tatsuya] Be honest with me,
Mikihiko.

00:03:23.741 --> 00:03:26.412
Just what do you really
envision yourself to be?

00:03:26.880 --> 00:03:27.982
That's hard to say.

00:03:28.416 --> 00:03:30.353
[Tatsuya] This idea that
no matter how many

00:03:30.420 --> 00:03:32.759
you're up against,
no matter how skilled they are,

00:03:32.826 --> 00:03:35.565
you can defeat them
without any help from anyone‐‐

00:03:35.631 --> 00:03:38.571
please don't tell me that
delusion guides your actions.

00:03:38.637 --> 00:03:39.806
[exhales]

00:03:40.373 --> 00:03:41.910
I'm not kidding.

00:03:42.478 --> 00:03:44.583
Do I really need
to say it again?

00:03:45.117 --> 00:03:46.787
[Tatsuya] You're being stupid.

00:03:46.854 --> 00:03:49.325
Why would you discredit yourself
to that degree?

00:03:50.060 --> 00:03:51.295
[chuckles]

00:03:51.362 --> 00:03:53.266
No offense,
but you wouldn't understand.

00:03:53.834 --> 00:03:55.538
There's nothing
I can do about it now.

00:03:55.605 --> 00:03:57.776
Actually, I think
that there might be a way.

00:03:57.842 --> 00:03:58.811
[Mikihiko] Huh?

00:03:58.878 --> 00:04:00.848
[Tatsuya] Now,
correct me if I'm wrong,

00:04:00.915 --> 00:04:03.721
but isn't it your casting speed
that you're worried about?

00:04:04.121 --> 00:04:05.390
[Mikihiko]
Did Erika tell you that?

00:04:05.457 --> 00:04:06.459
[Tatsuya] No.

00:04:06.527 --> 00:04:07.695
[Mikihiko] Then how do you know?

00:04:07.762 --> 00:04:09.398
There are too many
superfluous components

00:04:09.465 --> 00:04:10.434
to your spells.

00:04:10.501 --> 00:04:11.670
[Mikihiko] What do you mean?

00:04:11.737 --> 00:04:13.607
It's not a question
of your talent.

00:04:13.674 --> 00:04:15.277
I'm telling you that there's
a problem

00:04:15.343 --> 00:04:16.580
in the spells themselves.

00:04:16.647 --> 00:04:18.751
My spells are the result
of years

00:04:18.818 --> 00:04:21.322
of the Yoshida family's
relentless refinements, Tatsuya,

00:04:21.389 --> 00:04:22.559
and who are you to say?

00:04:22.625 --> 00:04:24.028
You've only seen them once
or twice!

00:04:24.094 --> 00:04:25.263
[Tatsuya] But I can still tell.

00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:26.867
Just by seeing them,

00:04:26.934 --> 00:04:29.138
I can read the content
of an activation sequence

00:04:29.205 --> 00:04:31.610
and analyze
the corresponding spell.

00:04:32.277 --> 00:04:33.681
That's impossible.

00:04:33.747 --> 00:04:35.183
You're lying,
aren't you?

00:04:35.250 --> 00:04:38.289
I'm telling the truth,
but if you don't believe me...

00:04:38.524 --> 00:04:40.293
‐ [Mikihiko] All right.
‐ Regardless,

00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:42.264
we should take care
of these guys right now.

00:04:42.732 --> 00:04:45.972
[Tatsuya] I'll stand guard here
so you can go get security.

00:04:46.038 --> 00:04:47.374
No problem.

00:04:48.143 --> 00:04:49.980
[whirring]

00:04:50.046 --> 00:04:51.683
[Mikihiko grunts]

00:04:52.619 --> 00:04:54.923
[Harunobu] You didn't pull
any punches with that advice.

00:04:56.159 --> 00:04:57.427
[Tatsuya] Major.

00:05:01.703 --> 00:05:04.743
For someone who's so indifferent
to other people, that's unusual.

00:05:04.810 --> 00:05:07.147
Not indifferent.
More like pragmatic.

00:05:07.749 --> 00:05:09.151
[Harunobu] He struck a chord
in you.

00:05:09.218 --> 00:05:10.655
I suppose it makes sense.

00:05:10.721 --> 00:05:13.393
That boy does seem
to share your inward struggles.

00:05:13.459 --> 00:05:14.963
[Tatsuya] No.
Personally,

00:05:15.030 --> 00:05:16.834
I've already grown beyond
those issues.

00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:17.902
Is that so?

00:05:17.969 --> 00:05:19.840
You must remember what
it was like, then.

00:05:20.207 --> 00:05:21.409
[Tatsuya exhales]

00:05:23.581 --> 00:05:25.083
<i>[Announcer] Welcome</i>
<i>to the National Magic</i>

00:05:25.150 --> 00:05:27.689
High School Goodwill Tournament
<i>of Magic Skills‐‐</i>

00:05:27.755 --> 00:05:29.893
<i>the Nine Schools Competition!</i>

00:05:30.528 --> 00:05:32.097
<i>It's the same old format.</i>

00:05:32.164 --> 00:05:34.101
<i>Five days each</i>
<i>of official matches</i>

00:05:34.168 --> 00:05:36.907
<i>and rookie competitions</i>
<i>for ten days total!</i>

00:05:36.974 --> 00:05:40.013
<i>This year all eyes will</i>
<i>be on First High School.</i>

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:42.084
<i>Will they get their third</i>
<i>straight title,</i>

00:05:42.150 --> 00:05:44.689
or will Third High School break
<i>that streak?</i>

00:05:44.756 --> 00:05:47.094
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>♪♪ 'Cause I'm a believer ♪♪</i>

00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:49.164
<i>♪♪ Soul fever jump, ah ♪♪</i>

00:05:49.231 --> 00:05:51.068
<i>[Taku Iwasaki's "Soul Fever"]</i>

00:05:51.135 --> 00:05:53.541
<i>[Tatsuya] Honoka,</i>
<i>how are you doing physically?</i>

00:05:53.607 --> 00:05:55.076
Feeling fine, thanks.

00:05:55.143 --> 00:05:57.682
All of our training really
built up my stamina.

00:05:57.749 --> 00:06:00.487
I've also been getting
a lot more sleep lately.

00:06:00.988 --> 00:06:03.493
Honoka's getting quite muscular
these days, you know?

00:06:03.961 --> 00:06:05.865
Come on!
Don't say it like that, please!

00:06:05.932 --> 00:06:07.602
I'm not planning
to bulk up into some kind

00:06:07.669 --> 00:06:08.871
of muscle woman!
‐ [chuckles]

00:06:09.371 --> 00:06:10.641
[stammers]
See?

00:06:10.708 --> 00:06:12.946
Now even Tatsuya's making fun
of me!

00:06:13.012 --> 00:06:15.250
The only reason he laughed
was because you chose

00:06:15.317 --> 00:06:16.520
a weird way to put it.

00:06:16.587 --> 00:06:17.789
Great.
You, too?

00:06:18.489 --> 00:06:19.491
It doesn't matter.

00:06:19.559 --> 00:06:20.895
I'm the odd one out anyway.

00:06:20.962 --> 00:06:21.964
Unlike you two,

00:06:22.030 --> 00:06:23.534
I'm not lucky enough
to have Tatsuya see

00:06:23.601 --> 00:06:25.470
my events and support me.

00:06:25.538 --> 00:06:26.940
That's only partly true.

00:06:27.007 --> 00:06:29.512
I'm going to fine tune your CAD
at Mirage Bat.

00:06:29.579 --> 00:06:31.583
What about
my Battle Board match?

00:06:31.650 --> 00:06:32.785
Can you take that on, too,

00:06:32.852 --> 00:06:34.756
or are you too busy
'cause Shizuku

00:06:34.823 --> 00:06:37.394
and Miyuki will have you
for both their events?

00:06:38.062 --> 00:06:40.568
[Tatsuya] Sorry,
but I did help you practice.

00:06:40.635 --> 00:06:42.004
We came up
with your battle plan together,

00:06:42.070 --> 00:06:43.540
so you're not being left out
at all.

00:06:43.607 --> 00:06:44.843
Uh, Tatsuya,

00:06:44.910 --> 00:06:46.312
I'm not sure if you're
just playing dumb,

00:06:46.379 --> 00:06:47.515
but that's not
what Honoka's trying

00:06:47.582 --> 00:06:48.784
to tell you right now.

00:06:48.851 --> 00:06:49.786
Oh, brother,

00:06:49.853 --> 00:06:51.155
honestly I think
you're being just

00:06:51.222 --> 00:06:52.190
a bit too clueless here.

00:06:52.257 --> 00:06:53.359
Eureka.

00:06:53.426 --> 00:06:55.063
The flaw
you never knew Tatsuya had.

00:06:55.130 --> 00:06:56.299
That he's a total stiff?

00:06:56.365 --> 00:06:57.467
[grunts]

00:06:57.535 --> 00:06:58.469
‐ Huh?
‐ [both gasping]

00:06:58.537 --> 00:06:59.839
[both grunting]

00:07:01.075 --> 00:07:02.311
[exhales]

00:07:02.377 --> 00:07:04.148
<i>[Announcer 2] Welcome</i>
<i>to the official girls</i>

00:07:04.214 --> 00:07:05.584
<i>Battle Board event.</i>

00:07:05.651 --> 00:07:07.689
<i>The third trial match</i>
<i>will begin shortly.</i>

00:07:08.122 --> 00:07:10.861
<i>Athletes,</i>
<i>please take your positions.</i>

00:07:13.366 --> 00:07:15.905
[Erika exhales]
She's just as snotty as ever.

00:07:16.305 --> 00:07:17.575
[both] Hmm?

00:07:17.642 --> 00:07:19.478
[Announcer 2] First High School
<i>third year,</i>

00:07:19.546 --> 00:07:20.982
<i>Miss Mari Watanabe.</i>

00:07:21.048 --> 00:07:24.956
[all chanting]
Mari, Mari, Mari, Mari, Mari!

00:07:25.023 --> 00:07:27.595
I see that she's got a lot
of devoted fans.

00:07:27.662 --> 00:07:29.398
It's understandable,
of course.

00:07:29.465 --> 00:07:32.037
Miss Watanabe's undeniably cool.

00:07:32.705 --> 00:07:34.709
[beeps]
<i>[Announcer 2] On your mark.</i>

00:07:36.212 --> 00:07:37.147
[gun fires]

00:07:37.214 --> 00:07:39.051
[all cheering]

00:07:39.118 --> 00:07:40.588
[grunts]

00:07:40.955 --> 00:07:41.757
[all shouting]

00:07:41.823 --> 00:07:43.560
[Erika] A self‐destruct spell?

00:07:43.627 --> 00:07:44.829
[Tatsuya] Most likely she tried
to throw off

00:07:44.896 --> 00:07:47.467
the other contestants
by creating a huge wave.

00:07:47.535 --> 00:07:49.004
Hey, they're catching up to her!

00:07:50.307 --> 00:07:52.712
[whirring]

00:07:54.983 --> 00:07:57.287
So she's applying
fortification magic

00:07:57.354 --> 00:07:58.857
while also casting movement?

00:07:59.224 --> 00:08:02.264
Fortifying magic?
But what is she strengthening?

00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:04.769
[Tatsuya] She's anchoring
her relative position

00:08:04.836 --> 00:08:07.007
to her board to keep
from falling off.

00:08:07.441 --> 00:08:09.044
‐ [Leonhard] Hmm?
‐ Put another way,

00:08:09.111 --> 00:08:11.850
fortification doesn't strengthen
a substance.

00:08:11.917 --> 00:08:14.889
It anchors components relative
to each other.

00:08:14.956 --> 00:08:17.060
Surely you understand that.

00:08:17.127 --> 00:08:19.666
Of course,
considering I use it myself.

00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:21.803
[Tatsuya] Miss Watanabe
made herself

00:08:21.870 --> 00:08:25.143
and her board a single object
comprising one component.

00:08:25.210 --> 00:08:28.049
The spell anchors
its relative position.

00:08:28.884 --> 00:08:31.422
She's casting movement magic
on herself and the board

00:08:31.489 --> 00:08:32.792
as a single entity.

00:08:32.859 --> 00:08:34.428
[Leonhard] How creative!

00:08:34.495 --> 00:08:35.664
[Tatsuya] Yes.

00:08:35.731 --> 00:08:37.267
It's quite
an interesting application.

00:08:38.336 --> 00:08:40.608
She's also using
vibration magic?

00:08:40.674 --> 00:08:42.210
That's impressive.

00:08:42.277 --> 00:08:44.448
She's multi‐casting three
to four different types

00:08:44.516 --> 00:08:45.785
of spells continuously.

00:08:50.393 --> 00:08:51.563
[all screaming]

00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:54.903
[grunts]

00:08:55.437 --> 00:08:56.907
She's quite the strategist.

00:08:56.973 --> 00:08:59.144
No, she just really hates
to lose.

00:08:59.746 --> 00:09:01.282
[Leonhard] Well,
it looks like she won't.

00:09:01.348 --> 00:09:02.250
[Tatsuya] Yep.

00:09:05.423 --> 00:09:07.662
[cicadas chirping]

00:09:09.866 --> 00:09:12.471
Excuse me, Major Kazama,
but you have a guest.

00:09:12.939 --> 00:09:14.007
<i>[Harunobu] Come in.</i>

00:09:15.911 --> 00:09:17.347
Reporting for duty.

00:09:17.815 --> 00:09:19.351
[Harunobu] Welcome.

00:09:19.719 --> 00:09:21.021
Please, have a seat.

00:09:21.088 --> 00:09:23.827
No, thanks.
I'll be fine right here.

00:09:24.194 --> 00:09:25.430
At ease, Tatsuya.

00:09:25.497 --> 00:09:28.871
We didn't call you here today
as special officer

00:09:28.937 --> 00:09:32.277
and the strategic class magician
Ryuuya Ooguro.

00:09:32.344 --> 00:09:33.747
When we invited you here,

00:09:33.814 --> 00:09:36.252
it was as our personal friend
Tatsuya Shiba.

00:09:36.853 --> 00:09:38.891
[Shigeru] If you stand there
before us formally,

00:09:38.957 --> 00:09:40.460
we won't know what to do.

00:09:40.528 --> 00:09:42.230
Ah, my apologies.

00:09:42.865 --> 00:09:45.203
Captain Sanada,
forgive me.

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:54.221
[Kyouko] These tea cups don't
quite capture the spirit...

00:09:55.356 --> 00:09:56.760
But how about a toast?

00:09:58.095 --> 00:09:59.866
[Harunobu]
About last night's incident.

00:09:59.933 --> 00:10:01.870
There's no question
those intruders

00:10:01.937 --> 00:10:04.576
were with the No Head Dragons
I told you about.

00:10:04.943 --> 00:10:07.515
[Tatsuya] Are they targeting
the NSC as suspected?

00:10:07.582 --> 00:10:09.552
That's still being investigated.

00:10:10.086 --> 00:10:11.823
[Harunobu] You'll be kept
in the loop.

00:10:12.424 --> 00:10:13.660
Much appreciated.

00:10:13.727 --> 00:10:14.963
[Kyouko] Still, I'm amazed
that you happened

00:10:15.029 --> 00:10:16.600
to be right there
on the spot.

00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:18.937
Were you on the lookout
for something?

00:10:19.004 --> 00:10:21.543
I was taking a stroll
and that's when I happened

00:10:21.610 --> 00:10:22.945
to sense their presence.

00:10:23.012 --> 00:10:25.450
You went for a walk
at such a late hour?

00:10:25.951 --> 00:10:29.057
Well, I'd been out fine‐tuning
our CADs for the matches.

00:10:29.692 --> 00:10:30.895
[Kousuke] Oh, that reminds me.

00:10:30.961 --> 00:10:33.567
Do your teammates know
about silver?

00:10:33.934 --> 00:10:35.871
[Tatsuya] No, Major Yamanaka,

00:10:35.938 --> 00:10:38.209
since that is,
after all, confidential.

00:10:38.276 --> 00:10:40.113
[Kyouko] Are you competing
in any events?

00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:41.683
You know,
with your impressive

00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:42.885
Flash Casts skills,

00:10:42.952 --> 00:10:44.789
I bet that you'd do pretty well.

00:10:44.856 --> 00:10:47.127
Material Burst
is too destructive,

00:10:47.194 --> 00:10:49.532
although you could always use
Mist Dispersion.

00:10:49.933 --> 00:10:52.137
Releasing substances
at the molecular level

00:10:52.204 --> 00:10:55.578
as one does with Mist Dispersion
is a Rank A destructive spell

00:10:55.644 --> 00:10:57.615
so Tatsuya can't use it
at the NSC.

00:10:57.682 --> 00:10:59.686
Wait, what's this,
Major Sanada?

00:10:59.752 --> 00:11:01.590
I think
you've overlooked something.

00:11:02.090 --> 00:11:04.027
<i>[Kyouko] NCS restrictions</i>
<i>are placed upon events</i>

00:11:04.094 --> 00:11:06.533
that might have
personnel‐related repercussions,

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:08.570
<i>but Speed Shooting</i>
<i>and Ice Pillars Break</i>

